%section.dark.hero
  .container
    %h1= ENV['dashboard_title']

    %a.button{href: user_omniauth_authorize_path(:mediawiki)}
      %i.icon.icon-wiki-logo
      = t('home.log_in')

    %a.button.button-ghost.button-inverse{href: user_omniauth_authorize_path(:mediawiki_signup)}
      %i.icon.icon-wiki-logo
      = t('home.sign_up')

    %a.help{href: '/ask'} ?

%section
  .container.text-center
    %h2= @presenter.cohort.title

    = render 'courses/header_stats', presenter: @presenter

    %a.button.button-ghost{href: '/courses'}= t('home.explore')

%section.light
  .container
    %h2.h1 We cultivate learning that enriches Wikipedia and universities, creating a world where any learner can contribute to open scholarship and education for all.

%section
  .container
    %h2.text-center The dashboard provides easy to use tools for instructors and students

    .col
      %h3 Instructors
      %h2 Create and Manage a Wikipedia Assignment
      %ul
        %li Learn how to edit Wikipedia, create, and manage a course with our interactice training
        %li Create a course from our templates and refine the course to meet your needs.
        %li A clean interface for tracking the class’s progress

    .col
      %h3 Students
      %h2 Stay Informed and Learn How to Edit Wikipedia
      %ul
        %li Learn how to edit Wikipedia with our interactive training
        %li A single location to stay up to date with your Wikipedia assignment
        %li A clean interface for tracking your progress while editing Wikipedia

%section.dark.stats-total
  .container
    %h2.h1 Impact since 2010:

    %h3 Wiki Ed Courses
    %h4= 640

    %div
      .col
        %h3 Students
        %h4 14,000

      .col
        %h3 Articles worked on
        %h4 35,000

    %div
      .col
        %h3 Characters added
        %h4 20.5 Million
        %p
          The number of words students have donated to the world. That’s 28,000 pages – the equivalent of 28 volumes of a printed encyclopedia, shared with everyone, for free.

      .col
        %h3 Article views, in a single term
        %h4 69.4 Million
        %p
          How many people have read the Wikipedia articles these students have edited? In a single term, 69.4 million – larger than the population of France.

